modules.description: This module exposes internal rope structure details for validation and inspection during testing. It provides functions to convert ropes to S-expressions, count base string segments, and convert ropes to strings without stack overflow risks. Use it to verify correctness of rope transformations, debug structural properties, or test serialization logic.

This module implements a rope data structure for efficient string manipulation, optimized for lazy concatenation and incremental traversal. It supports operations like concatenation (`^`), prefix checking, and conversion to strings or character sequences, while working directly with tree-based string representations to avoid full copies during intermediate steps. Concrete use cases include building large strings from many fragments, streaming character output, and testing structural properties of ropes through internal inspection tools.
